Author: polycryptoblog#1173
Content: Hydro plants dam water to create enough head to generate force to move the impellers.  But that isn't storing power though.   If a generator isn't tapped at max capacity it isn't wasting power,  it's just that not being used to its full potential.   Basically every load that gets attached increases the amount of current drawn ( how parallel circuits work ) ,  generator windings can only handle so much current .  You push it you break the generator.   Force to turn impeller increases with amount of current drawn due to Fleming right hand rule.  Only ways to "store" electric is batteries and capacitors both have limitations on heavy sustained load applications.
